usage: git oreset [<options>]

Reset all local branches to match remote branches and prune tags.
WARNING: this command cancel unpushed modifications.

    -h|--help               display help
    -j<n>                   number of submodules synchronized in parallel (default to 32)
    -a|--all                visit all submodules (ignore SKU filter)
    -r|--recursive          visit submodules recursively
    -f|--force              discard unstaged changes and delete untracked files
    
example:
    git oreset              # reset clean working dir
    git oreset -f           # reset dirty working dir
    git oreset -r           # reset clean working dir and submodules recursively
    git oreset -r -f        # reset dirty working dir and submodules recursively